  "text": "where B R is the ACF of BOC signal, B/L R is the CCF between the received BOC signal and the local SCS signal, and α is the weight coefficient. It can be seen that (23) is similar with the SCF used in [CITATION_1] in form. However, as shown later, GRASS technique is not only suitable for BOC(n,n) signals but also for other BOC ( ) , kn n signals.",
